 Nigeria’s bench players gather for the national anthem during the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations (CAN) Round of 16 football match between Nigeria and Cameroon at the Alexandria Stadium in the Egyptian city on July 6, 2019. (Photo by JAVIER SORIANO / AFP)  Earlier in Alexandria, Nigeria had beaten Cameroon 3-2 against pundits’ predictions, but it was nowhere near the shock caused by the Bafana Bafana, who defeated Egypt 1-0 in Cairo. The South Africans, who did not show any sign of a side that barely managed to qualify for the second round, got their winner five minutes from time through Thembinkosi Lorch. South Africa will now meet Nigeria on Wednesday.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .